<p><b>Gábor Tardos</b> (born 11 July 1964) is a <a href="/wiki/Hungarian_people" title="Hungarian people" class="mw-redirect">Hungarian</a> <a href="/wiki/Mathematician" title="Mathematician">mathematician</a>, currently a professor and <a href="/wiki/Canada_Research_Chair" title="Canada Research Chair">Canada Research Chair</a> at <a href="/wiki/Simon_Fraser_University" title="Simon Fraser University">Simon Fraser University</a>. He works mainly in <a href="/wiki/Combinatorics" title="Combinatorics">combinatorics</a> and <a href="/wiki/Computer_science" title="Computer science">computer science</a>. He is the younger brother of <a href="/wiki/%C3%89va_Tardos" title="Éva Tardos">Éva Tardos</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
